<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
It should be done where there are safe areas, but as you adventure further out into the chaos of the deeper galaxy, you should get greater dangers from PVP.  However, this doesnt mean that they should eliminate good events from taking place in those more civil areas.  There should be just as much adventure that takes place within safe zones as there is out on the frontiers where life is a bit more dangerous.  Also, the fact is that there should be some other losses for pvp, maybe more like Asherons call, as far as looting, well, how can one make it so you dont lose a ton of good stuff?! the fact is its a hard thing to balance and I dont even have any good ideas for this issue.  But one thing is for sure, I hate the Bagging system, and I also hate the power looters even more.  EQ is just now looking at PVP issues.  Maybe with their new changes to EQ, we can expect to see a system that promotes a better PVP environment.  Lets face it .. without someone holding a persons hand and making sure we all play fair, its an almost impossible task to accomplish ..  <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"> <P>~&lt;Believing in the dream&gt;~
