<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Actually, Holo gave a really juicy tidbit on PvP. It won't be like EQ... Which I personally think is somewhat boring. The blue servers don't participate in PvP whatsoever while the red servers are full of cross teaming and item baggers. The way Holo put it sounds pretty good though, check it out:<BR>"We're shooting for having PvP be an optional but integral part of the overall experience. We will have done our jobs right if you, Shaithis, an avowed and self-described carebear, try it sometimes and LIKE it. The promise we are making to you is that *PvP will never come and GET you, you have to go find IT*. We're making one game here, not two. Our goal is "separate but equal" should you choose that route. But "Equal" does not mean "the same" and there will be things in PvP areas which are different from things in safe areas. You should be able to get along just fine without them, though."<P>When I go to E3 in two weeks hopefully I'll be able to milk some more info out of him. :P<P>Kivlan<P>--------------------<P>Kivlan<BR>Star Wars: Galaxies Realm Administrator<BR>http://swg.crgaming.com<BR>Kivlan@castersrealm.com
