I have characters on both PvP servers and blue servers and like both for different reasons.  On one hand, PvP is way more realistic.  You can't count on a "rule" in real life that says you can't have your faced smashed in by some big brute who just wants your money.  On the other hand, when I'm tired and just feel like going around and helping some of the newbies and lowlies with buffs, money or equipment, I will play a blue server.  I can't count the number of times I got waxed on a PvP.  It sucks sometimes, but there's no real disadvantage to this other than a time delay.<P>Star Wars should be 100% PvP though.  There should be consequences to this type of behavior.  Having the wildlands be PvP with no rules is awesome!  This creates a mini-quest which could result in higher level characters having to escort newbies around.  This could be a cool jedi quest for experience.  This is also good for pilots, who will be able to transport characters around by ship.<P>In cities, if reputable, a "APB" for a certain PK could go off.  Stormtroopers or rebels could then be on the lookout for the criminal and your only hope for survival is to take them on escape the city.  Totally Star Wars.<P>In relatively safe zones this could be enforced by sentry guards, droids or patrols with their NPC programming to actively look for player-killing.<P>It would be nice to see a morality scale also.  If someone is good at murdering people and not getting caught, they can start getting dark side points (or something like Dark Forces 2 or Mysteries of the Sith).  Vice versa on the light side points.  This info could then be accessed by a con.  If the character cons a certain grade of color... then they're a bad mofo that a low character should high-tail it away from.  thoughts?<P>Also, if reputation gets too bad, the characters will be posted on bounty hunter boards to be killed by any bounty hunter who is a part of a guild.  These PK's could appear as red-named to bounty hunters.  Too much killing of weak players could result in KOS everywhere, which would start to get really annoying after a while.<P>Looting should be all or nothing.  If you have steep enough penalties, players will be hesitant to kill a player.  Plus, if it's always PvP, a killed player could petition his guild to go get the PK and get the equipment back or a suitable credit amount.<P>Implementing elements like this into SWG will keep it the same level playing field for all and discourage the "raping" (as an earlier poster put it) of newbies.<P>DK
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#5d7790">
